(104, 1, '2015-04-07 10:53:24', '2015-04-07 15:53:24', '<h2>Our Different Programs &amp; Services</h2>\r\nWe offer a range of services to respond to the community needs and to teach clients how to change patterns of behavior and thoughts in order to achieve their maximum mental and emotional well-being. We offer initial assessments, medication management, individual, family, and marital therapy, as well as higher levels of care, such as partial hospitalization (PHP) and intensive outpatient (IOP) services for ages 6 and up. We also offer discharge planning for all clients and a school component for the children.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Partial Hospitalization (PHP):</h3>\r\nThis program is designed to provide safety/structure for clients while allowing them to go home at night, thus providing the least restrictive environment for recovery. It entails group therapy 4 hours per day, 5 days per week, individual therapy, med management, and family/couples sessions.\r\n<h3>Intensive Outpatient (IOP):</h3>\r\nThis is a step-down level of care for clients transitioning back to work or school. It entails at least 3 hours per day/3 days per week for adults and 4 hours per day/5 days per week for children, providing support and structure while clients integrate learned coping skills into the environment. Medication management, individual therapy and family/couples therapy are also incorporated, as needed. This is the step-down level of care from PHP, to transition the client back to work/school and life’s activities.\r\n\r\nSome clients are admitted directly to IOP, when their symptoms are not severe enough to warrant PHP, but severe enough that the client is having difficulty functioning without more structured support and intervention. A therapist will discuss these options during the initial assessment.\r\n<h3>Medication Management:</h3>\r\nClients are provided an evaluation and monitoring by a psychiatrist for medications, adverse reactions, and side effects to reduce their current mental health symptoms. When in PHP, they see the psychiatrist a minimum of twice/week and in IOP, once/week.\r\n<h3>Initial Assessments:</h3>\r\nMAM offers initial assessments to understand the clients at a deeper level and direct them to the services they need. Please contact MAM today to schedule an assessment for you or your loved one.\r\n<h3>Discharge Planning:</h3>\r\nTo provide a smooth transition after discharging from the IOP/PHP programs, your counselor will work with you and/or the family to schedule appointments as needed, prior to discharge. Please see the "What to Expect at Admission" page for more information.\r\n<h3>School:</h3>\r\nWe ask that our clients remain in their home school on homebound curriculum while they are receiving care in our program. We provide an online accredited school component for our children and/or contact home schools weekly with attendance and reporting of grades. A MAM staff member will drop off school work and pick up new school work from the surrounding schools if the children are not being unenrolled from their current school.\r\n<h3>Our Groups</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Children</li>\r\n	<li>Adolescents</li>\r\n	<li>Adults</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive Outpatient (IOP)</li>\r\n	<li>Partial Hospitalization (PHP)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>SELF-EVALUATION CHECKLISTS</h2>\r\nPlease see the checklists below to give yourself and quick self evaluation.\r\n\r\n<a>Anxiety:</a>\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<div id="a1">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Anxiety and/or worry about a number of events, such as work, financial matters, school performance, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Difficulty in controlling the worry</li>\r\n	<li>Restlesness, feeling keyed up or on edge</li>\r\n	<li>Being easily fatigued</li>\r\n	<li>Difficulty Concentrating</li>\r\n	<li>Irritability</li>\r\n	<li>Muscle Tension</li>\r\n	<li>Restless sleep or difficulty falling or staying asleep</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you answered yes to three or more of the above, you may be suffering from generalized anxiety. There are more specific forms of anxiety, such as social phobia, panic, and post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD).\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a>Panic:</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="a2">\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sweating</li>\r\n	<li>Rapid heartbeat</li>\r\n	<li>Nausea, stomach cramps</li>\r\n	<li>Shortness of breath, feeling of being smothered</li>\r\n	<li>Chest pain</li>\r\n	<li>Numbness</li>\r\n	<li>Feelings of disconnection or unreality</li>\r\n	<li>Hot or cold flashes</li>\r\n	<li>Fear of dying, losting control or going crazy</li>\r\n	<li>Trembling or shaking</li>\r\n	<li>Feeling of choking</li>\r\n	<li>Dizziness or light-headedness</li>\r\n	<li>Feeling detached from oneself (depersonalization)</li>\r\n	<li>Fear of leaving your home</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you have experienced four or more of these symptoms during a relatively brief time (less than 10 minutes), you may have had a panic attack.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a>Social Phobia:</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="a3">\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Fear of social situations in which you are exposed to unfamiliar people or possible scrutiny by others</li>\r\n	<li>In social situations, fear you will act in a way (or show anxiety symptoms) that will cause embarassment</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to feared social situation provokes anxiety and/or panic</li>\r\n	<li>You recognize your social fear to be excessive or unreasonable</li>\r\n	<li>Avoidance or dread of feared social situation</li>\r\n	<li>Fear of social or performance situations interferes with your normal routine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a>Depression:</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="a4">\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sad or empty mood</li>\r\n	<li>Loss of pleasure in activities you normally enjoy</li>\r\n	<li>Weight loss or weight gain, diminished or increased appetite</li>\r\n	<li>Sleep difficulties, too much or too little sleep</li>\r\n	<li>Feelings of restlessness or being slowed down</li>\r\n	<li>Fatigue or loss of energy</li>\r\n	<li>Feelings of worthlessness or guilt</li>\r\n	<li>Indecisveness, or diminshed ability to think or concentrate</li>\r\n	<li>Recurrent thoughts of death or suicide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you answered yes to five or more of the above, you may very likely be suffering from depression.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Programs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-07 10:53:24', '2015-04-07 15:53:24', '', 11, 'http://dev.mindabovematter.com/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(105, 1, '2015-04-07 11:02:24', '2015-04-07 16:02:24', '<h2>Intake and Admission Process:</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Process begins with an initial call to our office. This is either done by the patient/guardian or the referral source. Once contact is made, the office will schedule an initial intake assessment. An assessment by a licensed therapist must be completed before any services, including medication management, can begin.</li>\r\n	<li>Patient/guardian is to arrive 10-15 minutes before appointment to complete intake packet and consents. Intake paperwork is also available for download via our website, www.innovativepsych.org . Front office will obtain a copy of ID and insurance card for our records, as well as copies of any other pertinent documentation (i.e. IEP, previous assessments, or recent testing).</li>\r\n	<li>When intake packet is complete, the therapist will take patient/guardian to assessment room for intake interview. If patient is a minor, guardian must be present for at least a portion of the interview. At times, it is necessary for the therapist to gather additional information by meeting with the patient or guardian alone.</li>\r\n	<li>After interview is complete, therapist will educate on the programs and review recommendations for treatment with patient/guardian.</li>\r\n	<li>Patient/guardian will have follow up appointment scheduled within the recommended program and will receive a reminder of appointment time. Patient/guardian will be able to meet with our financial advisor at this time as well.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>We look forward to working with you!</strong>\r\n\r\n[zilla_button url="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/schedule" style="link" size="large" type="round" target="_self"] Schedule Appointment [/zilla_button] [zilla_button url="tel:8174473001" style="link" size="large" type="round" target="_self"] Call (817)447-3001 [/zilla_button]\r\n\r\n<strong>Main Office:</strong> 621 SW Johnson Avenue, Suite D, Burleson, Texas 76028\r\n<strong>Satellite:</strong> 800 W Airport Freeway, Suite 810, Irving, Texas 75062', 'What To Expect', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-to-expect', '', '', '2015-04-22 14:50:46', '2015-04-22 19:50:46', '', 0, 'http://dev.mindabovematter.com/?page_id=105', 0, 'page', '', 0),
