(151, 1, '2015-04-07 12:44:32', '2015-04-07 17:44:32', '<h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>\r\nWe know that you probably have questions about what we offer. Please look at the frequently asked questions below and try to find your answer. If you still don\'t see the answer to the question that you have please feel free to <a title="Contact Us" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/contact-us/">contact us</a>. Thank you.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Does Therapy Work?</h4>\r\n<div id="a1">MAM believes in the power of counseling and understands the benefits and needs of medication. It has been observed that those who actively work toward their therapy will see better results in the end. In 1995, Consumer Reports conducted a study examining the efficacy of therapy. Of the 4,000 therapy clients who responded, nearly 90% reported that they were managing life better after getting help. Those individuals who reported the most discomfort and upset at the beginning of treatment reported the most improvement from psychotherapy.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h4>How long will I need to be in treatment?</h4>\r\n<div id="a2">Our program is typically 6-8 weeks, depending on the client’s progress and clinical need for treatment.</div>\r\n<h4>How often will I need to attend treatment?</h4>\r\n<div id="a3">This is dependent on which program is recommended for you after an initial assessment and the severity of your current symptoms. The admissions counselor can answer this question after an intake assessment has been completed.</div>\r\n<h4>How will I be able to measure my progress in treatment?</h4>\r\n<div id="a4">Treatment plans will be updated bi-weekly and discussed with client or legal guardian to keep client updated on treatment progress and discharge date.</div>\r\n<h4>What insurance plans are accepted?</h4>\r\n<div id="a5">We accept the majority of all major insurance companies.</div>\r\n<h4>When do I pay?</h4>\r\n<div id="a6">Copayments, deductibles and