(275, 1, '2015-04-22 16:12:02', '2015-04-22 21:12:02', '<h2>Our Different Programs &amp; Services</h2>\r\nWe offer a range of services to respond to the community needs and to teach clients how to change patterns of behavior and thoughts in order to achieve their maximum mental and emotional well-being. We offer initial assessments, medication management, individual, family, and marital therapy, as well as higher levels of care, such as partial hospitalization (PHP) and intensive outpatient (IOP) services for ages 6 and up. We also offer discharge planning for all clients and a school component for the children.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Partial Hospitalization (PHP):</h3>\r\nThis program is designed to provide safety/structure for clients while allowing them to go home at night, thus providing the least restrictive environment for recovery. It entails group therapy 4 hours per day, 5 days per week, individual therapy, med management, and family/couples sessions.\r\n<h3>Intensive Outpatient (IOP):</h3>\r\nThis is a step-down level of care for clients transitioning back to work or school. It entails at least 3 hours per day/3 days per week for adults and 4 hours per day/5 days per week for children, providing support and structure while clients integrate learned coping skills into the environment. Medication management, individual therapy and family/couples therapy are also incorporated, as needed. This is the step-down level of care from PHP, to transition the client back to work/school and life’s activities.\r\n\r\nSome clients are admitted directly to IOP, when their symptoms are not severe enough to warrant PHP, but severe enough that the client is having difficulty functioning without more structured support and intervention. A therapist will discuss these options during the initial assessment.\r\n<h3>Medication Management:</h3>\r\nClients are provided an evaluation and monitoring by a psychiatrist for medications, adverse reactions, and side effects to reduce their current mental health symptoms. When in PHP, they see the psychiatrist a minimum of twice/week and in IOP, once/week.\r\n<h3>Initial Assessments:</h3>\r\nMAM offers initial assessments to understand the clients at a deeper level and direct them to the services they need. Please contact MAM today to schedule an assessment for you or your loved one.\r\n<h3>Discharge Planning:</h3>\r\nTo provide a smooth transition after discharging from the IOP/PHP programs, your counselor will work with you and/or the family to schedule appointments as needed, prior to discharge. Please see the "What to Expect at Admission" page for more information.\r\n<h3>School:</h3>\r\nWe ask that our clients remain in their home school on homebound curriculum while they are receiving care in our program. We provide an online accredited school component for our children and/or contact home schools weekly with attendance and reporting of grades. A MAM staff member will drop off school work and pick up new school work from the surrounding schools if the children are not being unenrolled from their current school.\r\n<h3>Our Groups</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Children</li>\r\n	<li>Adolescents</li>\r\n	<li>Adults</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive Outpatient (IOP)</li>\r\n	<li>Partial Hospitalization (PHP)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Self-Evaluation Checklist</h2>\r\nPlease see the checklists below to give yourself and quick self evaluation.\r\n\r\n<a>Anxiety:</a>\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<div id="a1">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Anxiety and/or worry about a number of events, such as work, financial matters, school performance, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Difficulty in controlling the worry</li>\r\n	<li>Restlesness, feeling keyed up or on edge</li>\r\n	<li>Being easily fatigued</li>\r\n	<li>Difficulty Concentrating</li>\r\n	<li>Irritability</li>\r\n	<li>Muscle Tension</li>\r\n	<li>Restless sleep or difficulty falling or staying asleep</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you answered yes to three or more of the above, you may be suffering from generalized anxiety. There are more specific forms of anxiety, such as social phobia, panic, and post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD).\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a>Panic:</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="a2">\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sweating</li>\r\n	<li>Rapid heartbeat</li>\r\n	<li>Nausea, stomach cramps</li>\r\n	<li>Shortness of breath, feeling of being smothered</li>\r\n	<li>Chest pain</li>\r\n	<li>Numbness</li>\r\n	<li>Feelings of disconnection or unreality</li>\r\n	<li>Hot or cold flashes</li>\r\n	<li>Fear of dying, losting control or going crazy</li>\r\n	<li>Trembling or shaking</li>\r\n	<li>Feeling of choking</li>\r\n	<li>Dizziness or light-headedness</li>\r\n	<li>Feeling detached from oneself (depersonalization)</li>\r\n	<li>Fear of leaving your home</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you have experienced four or more of these symptoms during a relatively brief time (less than 10 minutes), you may have had a panic attack.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a>Social Phobia:</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="a3">\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Fear of social situations in which you are exposed to unfamiliar people or possible scrutiny by others</li>\r\n	<li>In social situations, fear you will act in a way (or show anxiety symptoms) that will cause embarassment</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to feared social situation provokes anxiety and/or panic</li>\r\n	<li>You recognize your social fear to be excessive or unreasonable</li>\r\n	<li>Avoidance or dread of feared social situation</li>\r\n	<li>Fear of social or performance situations interferes with your normal routine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a>Depression:</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="a4">\r\n\r\nDo you currently suffer, or have you suffered from the following?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sad or empty mood</li>\r\n	<li>Loss of pleasure in activities you normally enjoy</li>\r\n	<li>Weight loss or weight gain, diminished or increased appetite</li>\r\n	<li>Sleep difficulties, too much or too little sleep</li>\r\n	<li>Feelings of restlessness or being slowed down</li>\r\n	<li>Fatigue or loss of energy</li>\r\n	<li>Feelings of worthlessness or guilt</li>\r\n	<li>Indecisveness, or diminshed ability to think or concentrate</li>\r\n	<li>Recurrent thoughts of death or suicide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you answered yes to five or more of the above, you may very likely be suffering from depression.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="a4">[zilla_button url="/schedule" style="link" size="large" type="round" target="_self"] Schedule Your Appointment [/zilla_button] [zilla_button url="/what-to-expect" style="grey" size="large" type="round" target="_self"] What To Expect [/zilla_button]</div>', 'Programs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-22 16:12:02', '2015-04-22 21:12:02', '', 11, 'http://dev.mindabovematter.com/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(276, 1, '2015-04-22 16:16:51', '2015-04-22 21:16:51', '<h2>About Our Staff</h2>\r\nMAM offers a multi-disciplinary team to ensure collaborative care is achieved. We have a range of specialists available to help diagnose and guide you to a healthier you. MAM strongly believes that an organization is only as great as it\'s team and we pride ourselves on bringing you highly trained professionals to serve you.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Meet Our Team</h2>\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-123 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/jenny.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Jenny Kincaid" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#jenny">Jenny Kincaid</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">LCSW, CEO</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-128 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/raquel.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Raquel Harper" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#raquel">Raquel Harper</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">VP of Operations</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third" last="true"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-129 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/reshaunda.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Reshaunda Strickland" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#reshaunda">Reshaunda Strickland</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">PsyD, Child/Adolescent Director</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-121 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/jackie.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Jackie Todd" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#jackie">Jackie Todd</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">LPC-Intern, Unit Therapist</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-119 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/erin.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Erin Johnson" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#erin">Erin Johnson</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">LPC-Intern, Unit Therapist</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third" last="true"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-127 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/nicole.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Nicole Moure" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#nicole">Nicole Moure</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Director of Admissions</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-118 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/brityni.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Brityni Pettigrew" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 id="brityni" style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#brityni">Brityni Pettigrew</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Director of Business Management</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-120 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/gina.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Gina Luera" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#gina">Gina Luera</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">LCDC, LPC-Intern\r\nUnit Therapist</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third" last="true"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-117 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/bransha.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Bransha Gardner" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#bransha">Bransha Gardner</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Contract Therapist</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-122 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/jamila.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Jamila Davis" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#jamila">Jamila Davis</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Irving Office Manager</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-125 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/melissa.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Melissa Askari" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#melissa">Melissa Askari</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Director of Business Development</p>\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third" last="true"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-124 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/letty.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Letty Rodriguez" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#letty">Letty Rodriguez</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Privacy Officer</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n[zilla_column column="one-third" last="true"]\r\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-126 aligncenter" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/nick.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Nick Kincaid" width="121" height="107" />\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><a title="Staff" href="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/staff#nick">Nick Kincaid</a></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Financial Supervisor</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/zilla_column]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="jenny"><img class=" size-full wp-image-123 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/jenny.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Jenny Kincaid" width="121" height="107" />Jenny Kincaid</h3>\r\nLCSW, CEO\r\n\r\nJenny Kincaid is a licensed clinical social worker with 9 years combined experience in clinical and directorship roles. She left the corporate structure to found MAM, wanting to bring an innovative approach to MH delivery. Jenny holds a B.B.S. degree from Hardin Simmons University and Master of Science in Social Work degree from the University of Texas in Arlington. She has worked in a wide-range of service settings, including Hospices, Nursing Homes, Psychiatric Hospitals, Private-Practice, and Home Health. Jenny is most passionate about ensuring that quality and effective MH services be available to everyone, regardless of geographic location.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="raquel"><img class=" size-full wp-image-128 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/raquel.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Raquel Harper" width="121" height="107" />Raquel Harper</h3>\r\nVP of Operations\r\n\r\nRaquel Harper is the VP of Operations for MAM. She has a Bachelor\'s degree in Applied Liberal Arts with a major in Criminal Justice. Raquel brings years of experience in a vast array of MH settings to MAM. She has led teams in multiple organizations and is highly regarded for her administrative prowess. She ensures all the state, federal, and local regulations are strictly complied with and is passionate about ensuring ethical standards are complied with.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="reshaunda"><img class=" size-full wp-image-129 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/reshaunda.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Reshaunda Strickland" width="121" height="107" />Reshaunda Strickland</h3>\r\nPsyD, Child/Adolescent Director\r\n\r\nReshaunda Strickland, PsyD is a Postdoctoral Fellow, and she is currently pursuing licensure in the State of Texas. She has a Bachelor’s of Science degree in Psychology from Stephen F. Austin State University and a Doctor of Psychology degree from Argosy University-Dallas. She has extensive training and experience with psychological and neuropsychological assessments. Additionally, she has broad-based experience with individual counseling, family counseling, and psychoeducational programs. Other areas of experience include working with the developmentally disabled, severely mentally ill, and developing behavior modification programs. Dr. Strickland uses a client- and family- centered approach to therapy. She likes to focus on finding solutions to the problems her clients are facing. Her theoretical approach includes Cognitive-Behavioral Therapy, which helps clients understand the relationship between their thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. Dr. Strickland believes in taking the journey with her clients as they work towards achieving their goals and making lifelong changes.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="jackie"><img class=" size-full wp-image-121 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/jackie.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Jackie Todd" width="121" height="107" />Jackie Todd</h3>\r\nLPC-Intern, Unit Therapist\r\n\r\nJackie Todd is a Licensed Professional Counselor Intern (LPC-Intern) in the State of Texas, under the supervision of Dr. Tanisha Guy, NCC, LPC-Supervisor. She is also a Licensed Chemical Dependency Counselor Intern, currently studying for her exams. She has a Bachelor of Arts in Psychology from The University of Mary Hardin-Baylor and a Master’s of Science in Clinical Mental Health Counseling from The University of North Texas. She has extensive training in crisis intervention and assessment/diagnostic and has experience in individual, group, and couples counseling. She also has experience working with substance abuse and dual diagnosed. Jackie is a goal-oriented, problem-focused therapist with the belief that if we can learn to control and change our thoughts, our emotions and behaviors will follow. Her theoretical approach includes cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT), which is a goal-oriented theory and is an evidenced based treatment for mental health.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="erin"><img class=" size-full wp-image-119 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/erin.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Erin Johnson" width="121" height="107" />Erin Johnson</h3>\r\nLPC-Intern, Unit Therapist\r\n\r\nErin Wall-Johnson is a Licensed Professional Counselor Intern (LPC-Intern) in the State of Texas, under the supervision of Dr. Sean Stokes, PhD, LMFT-S, LPC-Supervisor. She has a Bachelor of Science in Psychology with a minor in English from Texas Christian University and a Master of Science in Marriage and Family Therapy and Professional Counseling from Texas Wesleyan University. She is passionate about working with individuals, couples, adolescents and families and believes in a collaborative, creative approach to therapy while creating a safe therapeutic environment that promotes hope and healing. Erin believes in an Emotionally Focused therapeutic approach designed to strengthen relationship bonds and help adolescents, couples, individuals and families develop emotional maturity and improve/repair attachment bonds in a safe, nurturing environment. Her theoretical approach also includes Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT), which is a goal-oriented theory and is an evidenced based treatment for improving mental health.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="nicole"><img class=" size-full wp-image-127 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/nicole.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Nicole Moure" width="121" height="107" />Nicole Moure</h3>\r\nDirector of Admissions\r\n\r\nNicole R. Mouré is a Licensed Professional Counselor (LPC) in the State of Texas. She has a Bachelor of Arts in Psychology and a Master of Arts in Professional Counseling, both from Argosy University in Phoenix, Arizona. She has extensive training in assessment and diagnostics, training as an intensive case manager, and experience in individual, group, and family therapy. Nicole\'s approach to counseling is strength-based and multi-systemic. Her theoretical approaches include cognitive behavioral, play therapy, solution-focused, and EMDR (Level 1 Certified). She believes in the importance of collaborating with and supporting her clients and their families as they make changes and life adjustments to reach their goals.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="brityni"><img class=" size-full wp-image-118 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/brityni.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Brityni Pettigrew" width="121" height="107" />Brityni Pettigrew</h3>\r\nDirector of Business Management\r\n\r\nBrityni Pettigrew is the Director of Business Management for MAM. She has a Bachelor of Science in Education from Liberty University and is currently studying for her certification exam. She enjoys working with children of all ages and has extensive experience working as a lead teacher for child development in a school setting.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="gina"><img class=" size-full wp-image-120 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/gina.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Gina Luera" width="121" height="107" />Gina Luera</h3>\r\nLCDC, LPC-Intern\r\nUnit Therapist\r\n\r\nGina Luera is a Licensed Professional Counselor Intern based in Texas, under the supervision of LPC-Supervisor Cherry Weaver. Ms. Luera specializes in substance-abuse counseling for parolees and probationers. Ms. Luera has accrued a wide-range of experience, including: recovery groups, cognitive-therapy groups, dual-diagnosis groups, relapse groups, IOP groups, inpatient and outpatient care, and partial hospitalization. Ms. Luera espouses client-centered counseling, meeting the client on their psychological level, positive psychology, and motivational interviewing. Theoretical approaches used by Mrs. Luera are solution focused and based in cognitive-behavioral therapy, transactional analysis, existensial / logotherapy, and client-centered therapy, as determined by the needs and world view of the client. Being Mexican-American, she is sensitive to the multi-cultural needs of her clients and embraces their diversity. Mrs. Luera holds a Bachelors of Arts in English and American Literature with a minor in Secondary Education, and a Masters of Science in Clinical Mental Health Counseling with a certificate in Advanced Addictions. She also holds an LCDC license in the State of Texas as well as being a Nationally Certified Counselor. She is currently seeking acceptance from Oregon State University for a Ph.D in Counseling.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="bransha"><img class=" size-full wp-image-117 alignleft" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/bransha.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Bransha Gardner" width="121" height="107" />Bransha Gardner</h3>\r\nContract Therapist\r\n\r\nBransha N. Gardner is a Licensed Professional Counselor (LPC) in the State of Texas and Louisiana. She has a Bachelor of Science in Family Consumer Science from Southern University and a Master of Arts in Counseling and Guidance from Louisiana Tech University. She has experience in individual, group, and family therapy. Her theoretical approaches include trauma focused cognitive behavioral, cognitive behavioral, play therapy, and solution-focused therapy. She describes the therapeutic relationship between a counselor and client as a collaborative one. The client and the counselor should work together to set goals that will help enhance the clients’ wellbeing and establish healthier patterns of relating to one’s self and others.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="jamila"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-122" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/jamila.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Jamila Davis" width="121" height="107" />Jamila Davis</h3>\r\nIrving Office Manager\r\n\r\nJamila Davis has experience in a hospital/clinic setting and desires to provide the best care to her clients. She currently operates in reception, and is eager to provide the best care for clients.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="melissa"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-125" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/melissa.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Melissa Askari" width="121" height="107" />Melissa Askari</h3>\r\nDirector of Business Development\r\n\r\nMelissa Askari is the Business Development Director for Mind Above Matter. She graduated from The University of Texas-Arlington with a Bachelor of Science in Biology. She has worked in the healthcare field for over 10 years, and compassionately understands the dynamics of working with a mental health facility. Her focus is to meet the needs of the community.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="letty"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-124" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/letty.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Letty Rodriguez" width="121" height="107" />Letty Rodriguez</h3>\r\nPrivacy Officer\r\n\r\nLeticia Rodriguez is the Privacy Officer for MAM. She has a certification in Medical Administrative Assistant from Everest College. She loves to provide excellent customer service, as well as to meet the individual needs of our clients.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 id="nick"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-126" src="http://dev.mindabovematter.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/nick.jpg" alt="Mind Above Matter Staff - Nick Kincaid" width="121" height="107" />Nick Kincaid</h3>\r\nFinancial Supervisor\r\n\r\nNick Kincaid is the Director of Plant Ops/Financial Services and currently serves as the Security Officer for MAM. He has been an integral part in establishing MAM and maintaining it\'s growth. Nick attended Hardin Simmons University, majoring in Business. Nick pulls from his experiences in his collegiate sports career along with his training in Business to oversee the financial services and plant operations aspects of the business.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[zilla_button url="/schedule" style="link" size="large" type="round" target="_self"] Schedule Your Appointment [/zilla_button] [zilla_button url="/what-to-expect" style="grey" size="large" type="round" target="_self"] What To Expect [/zilla_button]', 'Staff', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-22 16:16:51', '2015-04-22 21:16:51', '', 6, 'http://dev.mindabovematter.com/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
